<TITLE> Zonal-phase men's handball matches start Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 2 (bdnews24.com) - The zonal phase of the National Men's Handball Championship will get underway in Rangpur on Saturday with a record number of teams participating. As many as 29 districts, split into three zones, will play the group-phase matches with the champions and the runners-up from each zone qualifying for the 10-team final round to be held in Dhaka in May. The champions and the runners-up will join Bangladesh Rifles, Bangladesh Police, Bangladesh Ansar and Rajshahi DSA, the semifinalists of the last year meet. The matches of Kha zone comprising 12 districts will start on April 17 in Jessore while Ga zone consisting of nine districts will begin on April 28 in Rangamati. The Bangladesh Handball Federation revealed this at a press conference on Thursday. BHF president Nurul Fazle Bulbul said that they intended to hold an international handball tournament in Bangladesh in the coming winter season. "The tournament will be titled the Bangabandhu International Handball Tournament where 20 to 25 nations, some of them from Europe, will take part in the meet," said Bulbul. The BHF president said the prime minister appreciated their initiative and the EXIM Bank, a partner of the handball federation, was keen to sponsor the international tournament. EXIM Bank additional managing director Ekramul Haq said that they would continue to promote handball in a bid to make it popular among the younger generation. Chairman of the meet principal Hamida Ali and secretary Hasanullah Khan Rana also spoke on the occasion. Participating teams: Zone Ka: Joypurhat, Chapainawabganj, Panchaghar, Natore, Rangpur, Gaibandha, Bogra and Mymensingh. Zone Kha: Kushita, Jessore, Faridpur, Bagerhat, Patuakhali, Jhalakathi, Khulna, Madaripur, Gopalganj, Satkhira, Barisal and Narail. Zone Ga: Bandarban, Chittagong, Sunamganj, Chandpur, Rangamati, Chittagong Metropolis, Dhaka, Comilla and Bramanbaria. bd
